underlying_goal: To review staged changes and create logical, well-formatted git commits for the work done.
primary_success: Claude expertly followed complex instructions for a git workflow, correctly identifying distinct logical changes from a diff, splitting them into separate commits with clear messages, and providing the requested warning before offering to push.
brief_summary: The user invoked a custom /commit command. Claude analyzed the file changes, correctly identified that they represented logically distinct pieces of work (a migration to Bun, a new Netlify config, and a new blog post), and created two separate, well-messaged commits as a result.
